summary: This document is an email chain from November 2019 discussing scheduling a meeting to catch up on case developments. It references a recent interview in California that did not yield significant new information for a potential enticement charge and notes an upcoming proffer session with a witness.

events.title: Interview in California
events.description: A meeting was held in California with a potential victim/witness. The meeting did not add significant information, and it was determined an enticement charge was unlikely due to timing/location facts. The individual was unsure about pursuing a criminal case.

events.title: Upcoming Limited Proffer
events.description: A witness, referred to as 'Jane Doe 3', is scheduled for a limited proffer session to discuss her background.

keyFacts: An interview in California with a potential victim did not yield significant new information for the case.
Prosecutors determined they 'almost certainly couldn't bring an enticement charge' based on timing and location facts from the California interview.
The individual from the California meeting was still unsure about pursuing a criminal case.
A witness, Jane Doe 3, is scheduled for a limited proffer session to discuss her background.
The email chain is focused on scheduling a catch-up meeting among legal team members in November 2019.
